main event: Large, pulsing, a steaming mass of unknown material that came down from the east and was observed by a least 25 persons. AFOSI several minutes were needed to clear off a railroad rolling equipment.
interesting points: The object was observed to be approximately 12 feet in diameter, round in shape, and traveling at an estimated speed of 400-500 miles per hour.
The object was observed for approximately 2 minutes before it disappeared from sight.
The reported aerial phenomena are explainable as a meteorological balloon observed under unusual atmospheric conditions.
Two unidentified flying objects were sighted at Baltimore, Maryland (exact time not given) on approximately 28/1/1952.
A big ball of smoking bubbles descended on South Baltimore, and although it was only a few yards in diameter, it created quite a stir.
sighted object: Disc, round object, steaming mass of unknown material
